Subsequent sunrise view was worth it though!\r\n\r\nWas famished by the time I had my McD pitstop at Marine Cove even though I refueled 2x with energy bar.\r\n\r\nTMCR at 9am gave me a set of glorious tan lines.\r\n\r\nPost-100km was pure torture. Legs were pretty much jelly. Oh! And did I mention how my chain and sprocket were rattling? I think the previous downpour washed away too much of the wax-based lube. Sad...\r\n\r\nTried to endure but in the end had to \"cheat\" a little bit and cut across Sengkang PCN as Punggol decided to bless me with another localized downpour.\r\n\r\nEverything (bike computer, Apple Watch, taillight radar) was dying by the time I reached home. Managed to click \"save\" on both but Apple Watch somehow saved it late, so RIP heart rate data for Strava coz uploaded this using the Garmin data (thanks to me bringing a power bank and charging it at McD)!",

  "description": "Definitely felt stronger and more prepared than the first uphill ride I did earlier this year.\r\n\r\nPage Mill was totally fine, even though it was quite steep. Stage Rd uphill was also conquered with no issue even after riding for almost 50km when we tackled it. However, was not prepared at all for Tunitas Creek! The steep gradient of the mid-section was truly brutal - almost gave up entirely with the low morale and spent legs. However, pushed on through taking 3 mid-climb breaks and was rewarded with 2 popsicles at the top.\r\n\r\nLegs were well and truly spent on the way down, so even undulating mini climbs were painful. But we eventually made it back after rounding it up to 100km!\r\n\r\nPS: still need to figure out how to descend faster in a safe manner, I think I was too cautious and kept getting dropped by Alexey haha",

  "description": "Did this ride after a 10-hour delay caused by unexpected diversion to Guam (due to medical emergency) and then Honolulu (due to legal aviation restrictions). My trip went from a 14-hour direct to a 24-hour 2-layover flight \r\n\r\nVividly remembered dreading the last 10-minute of the 2nd climbing. \"Why did I do this to myself? When will this climb end? Will it ever end?\"  And then it rained during the final descent  Wore only a single layer so the cold wind cuts through the jersey  Thank goodness for disc brakes, really!\r\n\r\nUsing OLH as a benchmark (as do all Bay Area cyclist, apparently), still lots of room to grow. Took me 40 minutes going up, whereas seasoned cyclists took less than 30 minutes \r\n\r\nWelp, after all that,  will do it again. I guess this is what \"Type II Fun\" looks like ",
